Subject: [PATCH] ppu/include: the stub-archive workstream backfill — subdisplay + music* + imejp

Five new cell/sysutil_*.h forwarder headers landing as one batch
(per the the stub-archive workstream backfill plan).  All five are declaration-only
cell-SDK-name surfaces backed by self-contained stub archives produced
by `nidgen archive` and installed via scripts/build-cell-stub-archives.sh.

  - sysutil_subdisplay.h  — 11 exports (PSP-as-secondary-display)
  - sysutil_music.h       — 22 exports (XMB BGM playback, v1 + v2)
  - sysutil_music_decode.h— 20 exports (decode-to-memory, v1 + v2)
  - sysutil_music_export.h—  5 exports (track-export to XMB)
  - sysutil_imejp.h       — 41 exports (Japanese IME)

Total surface: 99 exports across 5 SPRX modules.  Music + music_decode
declare opaque forward types for SPURS / search / playback-common
struct dependencies — full layouts ship when the next sample needs
them.  imejp ships its full surface (no external type dependencies).

samples/hello-ppu-backfill/ links one symbol from each library into
a non-call sink so the FNID + sceResident entries land in the ELF
without runtime risk (the SPRX modules don't need to be LLE'd in
RPCS3 for this smoke test to pass — only the link-time machinery
matters).

